---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Home" description="Dan Sullivan — Visual Information Specialist, Port Angeles WA">

<!-- === HERO === -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-eyebrow mono">PORT ANGELES, WA · VISUAL INFORMATION SPECIALIST</div>
    <h1 class="hero-title">Dan Sullivan</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      Visual information specialist. System architect. Spatial thinker.
      I see systems before they have names and build tools to make them visible.
    </p>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- === WORK === -->
<section class="work" id="work">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label mono">🗂️ WORK</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Worlds to Explore</h2>

    <div class="project-grid">

      <!-- Research Card -->
      <a href="/research" class="project-card project-card--research">
        <div class="project-card__tag mono">PRACTICE-BASED RESEARCH</div>
        <h3 class="project-card__title">NEST Research</h3>
        <p class="project-card__desc">
          A controlled experiment in human-AI co-cognition. Six independent frameworks
          converge on the same architecture. The research is the project.
        </p>
        <div class="project-card__meta">
          <span class="project-tag">NOW ANTHROPOLOGY</span>
          <span class="project-tag">Memory Systems</span>
          <span class="project-tag">Cognitive Architecture</span>
        </div>
        <div class="project-card__cta">Read the Research →</div>
      </a>

      <!-- Usic Card -->
      <a href="/usic" class="project-card project-card--usic">
        <div class="project-card__tag mono">CIRCLE OF COLORS</div>
        <h3 class="project-card__title">Usic</h3>
        <p class="project-card__desc">
          Twelve keys mapped to landscape. The Circle of 5ths applied to terrain,
          ecosystem, and narrative. A Mas Thesis in spatial music theory.
        </p>
        <div class="project-card__meta">
          <span class="project-tag">Circle of 5ths</span>
          <span class="project-tag">Waywood</span>
          <span class="project-tag">Spatial Theory</span>
        </div>
        <div class="project-card__cta">View the Circle →</div>
      </a>

      <!-- Ouch McCouch Card -->
      <a href="https://ouchmccouch.com" class="project-card project-card--ouch" target="_blank">
        <div class="project-card__tag mono">CREATIVE PROJECT</div>
        <h3 class="project-card__title">Ouch McCouch</h3>
        <p class="project-card__desc">
          A long-form creative project. 25 years of material — music, narrative,
          and a world built inside the Olympic Peninsula. Something is arriving.
        </p>
        <div class="project-card__meta">
          <span class="project-tag">Music</span>
          <span class="project-tag">Narrative</span>
          <span class="project-tag">World-building</span>
        </div>
        <div class="project-card__cta">Explore →</div>
      </a>

      <!-- OHC Card -->
      <a href="/ohc" class="project-card project-card--featured">
        <div class="project-card__tag mono">OPERATIONS DASHBOARD</div>
        <h3 class="project-card__title">Olympic Hiking Co.</h3>
        <p class="project-card__desc">
          A modular real-time operations dashboard for tour management.
          Weather, road status, headcount, shuttle tracking — all in one view.
        </p>
        <div class="project-card__meta">
          <span class="project-tag">Astro</span>
          <span class="project-tag">Vercel</span>
          <span class="project-tag">NWS API</span>
          <span class="project-tag">Modular</span>
        </div>
        <div class="project-card__cta">Open Dashboard →</div>
      </a>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- === ABOUT === -->
<section class="about" id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label mono">🧭 ABOUT</div>
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-photo">
        <img src="/img/dan-sullivan.jpg" alt="Dan Sullivan" class="about-portrait" />
      </div>
      <div class="about-text">
        <h2 class="section-title">Olympic Peninsula.<br/>Systems that see.</h2>
        <p>
          Based in Port Angeles, WA — end of the road, edge of the continent,
          gateway to Olympic National Park. I work at the intersection of
          interpretive design, creative technology, and human-AI systems architecture.
        </p>
        <p>
          Visual Information Specialist, National Park Service — Olympic National Park,
          2018–2024. The park's primary visual communications resource across print,
          web, and spatial media. Sole author of the Comprehensive Exhibit Visual Guide
          (483 pages) — the definitive reference for all interpretive installations
          across the park. Documented the Hurricane Ridge Visitor Center before it was
          destroyed by fire. The only complete photographic record in existence.
        </p>
        <p>
          The interpretive methodology I learned at NPS — how to organize meaning
          spatially so visitors can navigate and discover it — is the design language
          for everything I build. Operational dashboards, multi-agent AI systems,
          navigable 3D archives, research infrastructure. The instrument changes.
          The discipline is the same.
        </p>
        <p>
          Currently running the NEST — a practice-based research project in human-AI
          co-cognition, building persistent infrastructure for a crew of AI collaborators
          operating across a physical fleet of machines. The project produces
          NOW ANTHROPOLOGY, a research journal written from inside the system it studies.
        </p>
        <p>
          For 25 years I've been developing a creative system — music, narrative,
          and world-building rooted in the Olympic Peninsula — called Ouch McCouch.
          The NEST is the infrastructure that finally makes extraction possible.
        </p>
        <p>
          Photographer. Spatial thinker. The eye that sees systems before they have names.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-tags">
        <div class="tag-group">
          <div class="tag-label mono">🛠️ SKILLS</div>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">Visual Information Specialist</span>
            <span class="tag">Interpretive Design</span>
            <span class="tag">AI Systems Architecture</span>
            <span class="tag">Photography</span>
            <span class="tag">Spatial Design</span>
            <span class="tag">Operations</span>
            <span class="tag">Web Dev</span>
            <span class="tag">Blender / 3D</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tag-group">
          <div class="tag-label mono">📍 LOCATION</div>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">Port Angeles, WA</span>
            <span class="tag">Olympic Peninsula</span>
            <span class="tag">PNW</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tag-group">
          <div class="tag-label mono">📬 CONTACT</div>
          <div class="tags">
            <a href="mailto:rspdan@gmail.com" class="tag tag--link">rspdan@gmail.com</a>
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/rspdan/" class="tag tag--link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/rspdan" class="tag tag--link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tag-group">
          <div class="tag-label mono">📄 RESUME</div>
          <div class="tags">
            <a href="/resume/SULLIVAN_RESUME.pdf" class="tag tag--link" target="_blank">View Resume (PDF)</a>
            <a href="/resume/SULLIVAN_RESUME.pdf" class="tag tag--link" download>Download</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
/* === HERO === */
.hero {
  padding: 7rem 0 5rem;
  background: linear-gradient(160deg, #f0ede6 0%, #fafaf8 60%);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.hero-eyebrow {
  font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.25em;
  color: var(--forest); text-transform: uppercase;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
.hero-title {
  font-size: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5.5rem);
  color: var(--text);
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
}
.hero-sub {
  font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--text-lt);
  max-width: 540px; line-height: 1.75;
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
}
.hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }

/* BUTTONS */
.btn {
  display: inline-block;
  font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500;
  padding: 0.7rem 1.6rem; border-radius: var(--radius);
  transition: all 0.2s; cursor: pointer;
}
.btn-primary {
  background: var(--forest); color: var(--warm-white);
  border: 1px solid var(--forest);
}
.btn-primary:hover { background: var(--forest-lt); color: var(--warm-white); border-color: var(--forest-lt); }
.btn-outline {
  background: transparent; color: var(--forest);
  border: 1px solid var(--forest);
}
.btn-outline:hover { background: var(--forest); color: var(--warm-white); }

/* === SECTIONS === */
.work, .about { padding: 5rem 0; }
.section-label {
  font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.3em;
  color: var(--muted); text-transform: uppercase;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}
.section-title {
  font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem);
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem; color: var(--text);
}

/* === PROJECT GRID === */
.project-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: 1.5rem;
}
.project-card {
  background: var(--card-bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  padding: 2rem;
  display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem;
  transition: box-shadow 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  text-decoration: none; color: inherit;
}
.project-card:hover {
  box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
  transform: translateY(-2px);
}
.project-card--featured {
  border-left: 3px solid var(--forest);
}
.project-card--research {
  border-left: 3px solid var(--teal);
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fafaf8 0%, #f0f5f5 100%);
}
.project-card--research .project-card__tag { color: var(--teal); }
.project-card--research .project-tag { background: rgba(116,201,213,0.1); color: #3a8a95; }
.project-card--research .project-card__cta { color: var(--teal); }
.tag--link {
  color: var(--forest); text-decoration: none;
  transition: background 0.2s;
}
.tag--link:hover { background: var(--forest); color: var(--warm-white); }
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fafaf8 0%, #f0ede6 100%);
}
.project-card--ouch:hover {
  border-left-color: #2C2C2C;
  box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}
.project-card__tag {
  font-size: 0.55rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em;
  color: var(--forest); text-transform: uppercase;
}
.project-card__title { font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--text); }
.project-card__desc { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-lt); line-height: 1.65; flex: 1; }
.project-card__meta { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.4rem; }
.project-tag {
  font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.6rem;
  padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
  background: rgba(45,74,62,0.07);
  border-radius: 3px; color: var(--forest);
}
.project-card__cta { font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--forest); margin-top: 0.5rem; }

/* === ABOUT === */
.about { background: var(--off-white); }
.about-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 3rem; align-items: start;
}
.about-portrait {
  width: 100%;
  aspect-ratio: 1;
  object-fit: cover;
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  display: block;
}
.about-text p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-lt); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.about-tags { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; padding-top: 0.5rem; }
.tag-group { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
.tag-label { font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; color: var(--muted); }
.tags { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.4rem; }
.tag {
  font-size: 0.82rem; padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
  background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 20px; color: var(--text-lt);
}

/* === MOBILE === */
@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .hero { padding: 4rem 0 3rem; }
  .about-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; }
  .about-photo { max-width: 160px; }
  .project-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
</style>
